PrecisEnactment of the ALBERTA EQUIVALENCY ORDER which declares that the provisions of the following federal Regulations made under the Canadian Environmental Protection Act do not apply in the Province of Alberta: . 1. Vinyl Chloride Release Regulations 2. Secondary Lead Smelter Release Regulations 3. Pulp and Paper Mill Effluent Chlorinated Dioxins and Furans Regulations 4. Pulp and Paper Mill Defoamer and Wood Chips Regulations (sections 4(1), 6(2), 6(3)(b), 7 and 9 only) .
